ce:section.ce:para:
Prior to the development of the integrated US and PA endoscope consisting of the miniaturized US transducer and light delivery (Fig. 1a), the capability of the US probe to detect PA signals and form images was tested in experiments where two phantoms were illuminated using an external light source (Fig. 3
                        ). For the first experiment, the system’s ability for creating a co-registered US/PA image was evaluated using a wire calibration phantom arranged laterally in a 10 cm cube container filled with water. For the test, five 200 μm diameter nylon wires were arranged in the pattern shown in Fig. 3
                        a and scanned using the endoscopic probe at a distance of 12 mm from wires in a water medium.
